<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 21 at 12:27AM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Madison
and Carroll Counties through 115 AM CDT...
At 1227 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm near
Eureka Springs, moving southeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects
is possible.
Locations in or near the path include...
Berryville...                     Eureka Springs...
Green Forest...                   Carrollton...
Rudd...                           Osage...
Urbanette...                      Rule...
Grandview...                      Rockhouse...
Dryfork...                        Cabanal...
Metalton...                       Connor...
Coin...                           Pleasant Ridge...
Denver...                         Oak Hill...
Delmar...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
